&lt;p&gt;I wanted to test out how good the tamron 90 was on flowers. Pretty damn sweet! These were shot in the Rose Garden at the Ringling Museum in Sarasota, Florida.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Shot with Pentax K-1000 with a Tamron Adaptall-2 SP 90mm f/2.5  on Kodak 160 nc-2. Scanned with Nikon Coolscan V ED. edited with Corel Photopaint.&lt;/p&gt;

