&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/kevinwakelam/4509020854/" title="Now That Spring Is Here !!!"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2173/4509020854_b3d68d6d09_m.jpg" width="240" height="162" alt="Now That Spring Is Here !!!" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://bighugelabs.com/onblack.php?id=4509020854&amp;amp;size=large" rel="nofollow"&gt;Best Seen Large On Black&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
What a pleasure it was to be able to go out and get a few flower shots.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
After what has seemed an endless winter, today's glorious sunshine and warm temperatures really lifted the spirits.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
I found this little beauty at Thornes Park in Wakefield.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/djbiesack/"&gt;gnuru&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/djbiesack/4512030278/" title="Bee on screen"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4004/4512030278_2c7f49c01e_m.jpg" width="240" height="150" alt="Bee on screen" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This bee got trapped between our window and the screen, so I took the screen down to let him out. He decided to to stay put and pose for a while before I let him off on a flowering bush.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/wolfraven/"&gt;wolfpix&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/wolfraven/4512594536/" title="Purple flower pollinator"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4024/4512594536_e9faa8fc51_m.jpg" width="240" height="238" alt="Purple flower pollinator" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Honeybee, &lt;i&gt;Apis mellifera&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
U.C. Davis Arboretum&lt;br /&gt;
Davis, California&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
I'd appreciate help on identifying the beautiful plant with the tiny purple blossoms which are shaped somewhat like orchids.  It was a broom-like bush or hedge with small leaves.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Looking at this title I gave the photo, I'm reminded of a pop song from my childhood -- &amp;quot;Purple people eater.&amp;quot;  &lt;b&gt;Wikipedia&lt;/b&gt; says this &amp;quot;novelty song&amp;quot; was written and sung by Sheb Wooley and was #1 on the Billboard charts in 1958.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/david-meadows/"&gt;DMeadows&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

