&lt;br /&gt;
I didn't make it back to the arboretum, but I did get out shooting in my neighborhood for a bit between the rains.  This is another handheld, which turned out a little better than the one I posted last night.  The center of this flower looked blown out for the most part, but I was able to use Lightroom's highlight recovery tool as well as some other techniques to extract some decent detail.  I also tried my hand at Photoshop CS5's content aware fill to partially get rid of a stalk in the lower right corner.  I'm trying full Photoshop for the first time right now on a thirty day trial, so my efforts are still pretty clumsy.  After a few aborted tries, I was able to mostly hide the stalk, though it's not nearly as smooth and unnoticeable as I'd like.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Cheers to everyone for the weekend, hope you enjoy the shot.  And, I should add, congrats to the USA for its tie with England in the World Cup.  One of these days, we're going to start actually beating the great teams of the world.&lt;/p&gt;

