&lt;p&gt;A gust of wind blew these little pollen away. For a minute, it looked as if they had sprouted wings and were flying from their home.&lt;br /&gt;
Every year in the month of June, the fields of Les Pléiades, Vevey, Switzerland are filled with sweet smelling narcissus flowers. Very few people seem to know about this. The fields are beautiful with these white wild flowers and the areas going through the fields pave way for a pleasant hike.&lt;/p&gt;

