&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/beckhusen/"&gt;Stefan Beckhusen&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/beckhusen/4803043806/" title="Green Bug 8334"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4081/4803043806_ba9e569ff5_m.jpg" width="240" height="192" alt="Green Bug 8334" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What a challenge to get a sharp shot of living insects in the wild ! &lt;br /&gt;
At first it needs time to find the right size and distance for the camera on tripod. Then the direct orientation of focus will be set. Then i've to wait for a short short moment without any wind ....... and hope this hungry bug will not change it's place for a moment. &lt;br /&gt;
All the while several flies and gen-manipulated moskitos made me crazy :[   &lt;br /&gt;
 The green bug is around 5 - 7 mm long. What you see of the flower is the white heart of a cornflower. &lt;br /&gt;
I have this scene also on video, but the sharpness is allways only for some seconds well.&lt;/p&gt;

